description: A brilliantly written graphic novel about the real human experience of living behind the iron curtain from one of Italy's leading comic artists.
name: Loss of Innocence

description: In the last leg of Celanawe's quest for the Axe and its meaning, he is led to discover a secret order of mice who guard its secrets and history, its maker, and others like him. The knowledge of his having recovered the Axe leads Celanawe to a difficult decision. The end of the issue holds one final surprise for longtime Mouse Guard fans! Features a pin-up by Mike Mignola (Hellboy).

description: Wally Wood's cover from Tales From the Crypt #26 wraps four classic stories from the EC Archives: Al Feldstein's "Spawn of Venus" from Weird Science #6; Alex Toth and Harvey Kurtzman's "Dying City" from Two-Fisted Tales #22; Johnny Craig's "Curse of the Full Moon" from Tales From the Crypt #17; and Wally Wood's "Under Cover" from Shock SuspenStories #6!

description: Reprints US Marvel Team-Up #79, where Spider-Man and Red Sonja battle Kulan Gath, plus Marvel Team-Up #100, featuring Fantastic Four and Spider-Man against Karma, plus the back-up story from that same issue, depicting the first meeting of the young Ororo Munroe and T'Challa.
Reprints Marvel US' Star Trek #11-12.

description: Reprints Marvel US' Star Trek #4-5. Despite the cover, there is no comic strip coverage of Star Trek: The Wrath of Khan.

description: Batman comes face-to-face with the man who killed his parents, but Superman is not going to allow The Dark Knight to carry out cold-blooded revenge. And just when things are about to get ugly, a new threat enters the picture--make that two new threats.
name: Detective Part 6
